vertible Preferred Stock was legally outstanding during historical periods prior to the xAI Merger and represented a separate equity class of a legally distinct predecessor entity, its conversion into SpaceX Common Stock is recognized *only* as of the closing of the xAI Merger. Consequently, historical consolidated balance sheets and equity statements reflect xAI\'s preferred stock in its legal form and are **not retrospectively recast** on an as-converted basis for periods prior to the xAI Merger Date. \n\n### 4. xAI Capital Structure (Following 2025 Articles of Incorporation Amendment)\nOn **March 28, 2025**, xAI adopted an Amended and Restated Articles of Incorporation (subsequently amended through January 30, 2026) which established its pre-merger capital structure:\n*   **xAI Common Stock:** Designated into three classes: Class A common stock ("xAI Class A"), Class B common stock ("xAI Class B"), and Limited Voting common stock ("xAI Limited Voting").\n*   **xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock:** Consisted of several series, categorized by voting rights:\n    *   *xAI Low Vote Stock:* Series A-1, B, C, D, and E.\n    *   *xAI High Vote Stock:* Series A.\n*   **Merger Conversion Mechanics:** Upon the xAI Merger, these preferred shares converted into SpaceX Common Stock based on a pre-2026 Stock Split exchange ratio of **0.1433 shares** of SpaceX Class A (for Low Vote) or Class B (for High Vote) per preferred share, rounded up to the nearest whole number. Eligible service providers holding Series A also had the option to elect a cash payout of $75.46 per share (on a pre-2026 split basis).',
