2026-06-09 16:09:50,715 DEBUG Tool call: submit_final_result({'final_result': '## Split-Adjusted Price Calculation\n\n**Pre-split secondary market peak price (Forge Global, April 1, 2026):** ~$634.00 per share\n**Stock split:** 5-for-1, effective May 4, 2026\n**Split-adjusted equivalent price:** $634.00 ÷ 5 = **$126.80 per share**\n\n---\n\n## Financial Statement Line Items Affected by Retroactive Split Adjustment\n\nThe SpaceX S-1 (filed May 20, 2026) explicitly states that **all share and per-share information** in the prospectus and consolidated financial statements has been **retroactively adjusted** to reflect the 5-for-1 stock split for **all periods presented**. The following specific line items and disclosures are directly affected:\n\n### 1. Earnings Per Share (Income Statement)\n- **Basic and diluted net income (loss) per share of common stock attributable to common shareholders** — All historical EPS figures are presented on a post-split basis. For example:\n  - FY2025 Basic/Diluted EPS: $(1.69)\n  - FY2024 Basic EPS: $0.01; Diluted EPS: $0.00\n  - FY2023 Basic/Diluted EPS: $(1.68)\n  - Q1 2026 Basic/Diluted EPS: $(1.27)\n  - Q1 2025 Basic/Diluted EPS: $(0.18)\n  \n  These per-share amounts are **5× lower** than they would have been on a pre-split basis, because the denominator (shares) is 5× larger.\n\n### 2. Weighted Average Shares Outstanding (EPS Denominator)\n- **Basic and diluted weighted average shares** used in computing EPS are all presented on a post-split (5× inflated) basis:\n  - FY2025: 2,926 million (basic); 2,926 million (diluted)\n  - FY2024: 2,848 million (basic); 9,956 million (diluted)\n  - FY2023: 2,759 million (basic and diluted)\n  - Q1 2026: 3,884 million (basic and diluted)\n\n### 3. Pro Forma EPS and Pro Forma Weighted Average Shares\n- **Unaudited pro forma basic and diluted net loss per share** (giving effect to the Preferred Conversion and Class C Reclassification):\n  - Q1 2026: $(0.41) on 10,607 million pro forma shares\n  - FY2025: $(0.51) on 9,649 million pro forma shares\n\n### 4. Pro Forma Net Tangible Book Value Per Share (Dilution Section)\n- The dilution table calculates **pro forma net tangible book value per share** as of March 31, 2026, which uses post-split share counts in its denominator. (Specific dollar values are blank in this preliminary S-1, pending pricing.)\n\n### 5. Authorized, Issued, and Outstanding Share Counts (Balance Sheet / Capitalization)\n- **Authorized shares:** 54,657 million total common stock shares (Class A: 36,132M; Class B: 6,125M; Class C: 10,000M; Class D: 2,400M)\n- **Issued and outstanding shares** for all classes of common stock\n- **Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock conversion rates** — proportionately adjusted so each preferred share is now convertible into **50 shares** of SpaceX Common Stock (previously 10 shares pre-2026-split)\n\n### 6. Statement of Changes in Stockholders\' Equity\n- All share issuance, repurchase, conversion, and retirement activity in the equity statement is restated to reflect post-split share volumes across all historical periods.\n\n### 7. Anti-Dilutive Securities Table\n- The count of potentially dilutive securities excluded from diluted EPS (preferred stock, stock options, RSUs, ESPPs) is presented in post-split share equivalents.\n\n### 8. xAI Merger Exchange Ratios\n- The xAI preferred-to-SpaceX common exchange ratio of **0.1433 shares** per xAI preferred share is stated on a **pre-2026 Stock Split basis**, requiring multiplication by 5 to arrive at the post-split equivalent (~0.7165 SpaceX shares per xAI preferred share).\n\n---\n\n## Why Analysts Must Apply the Adjustment Factor Before Drawing Valuation Conclusions\n\nAn analyst comparing pre-split secondary market transaction prices (e.g., Forge Global\'s ~$634/share peak on April 1, 2026) to post-filing per-share metrics **must** apply the 5-for-1 adjustment factor for the following critical reasons:\n\n### 1. Apples-to-Apples Comparability\nThe S-1 presents **all** per-share data on a retroactively split-adjusted basis. If an analyst naively compares the unadjusted $634 pre-split secondary price to the S-1\'s EPS of $(1.69) for FY2025, the implied P/E multiple would appear absurdly distorted. The correct comparison requires dividing the $634 pre-split price by 5 to arrive at **$126.80**, which is then comparable to the S-1\'s post-split EPS, book value per share, and other per-share metrics.\n\n### 2. Avoiding a 5× Valuation Error\nWithout adjustment, an analyst would overstate the price-to-earnings, price-to-book, and price-to-sales-per-share ratios by a factor of exactly 5. For example:\n- **Incorrect:** $634 ÷ $0.01 (FY2024 basic EPS) = 63,400× P/E\n- **Correct:** $126.80 ÷ $0.01 (FY2024 basic EPS) = 12,680× P/E\n\nWhile both multiples are high, the unadjusted figure is mathematically meaningless because the numerator (price) and denominator (EPS) are on different share-count bases.\n\n### 3. Consistency with Pro Forma and Dilution Metrics\nThe S-1\'s pro forma net tangible book value per share, pro forma EPS, and dilution calculations all use post-split share counts. Any valuation framework (DCF per share, comparable-company P/E, price/NTBV) that uses the S-1\'s per-share figures as the denominator must pair them with a split-adjusted price as the numerator.\n\n### 4. Preferred Stock Conversion Economics\nThe preferred stock conversion rate was proportionately adjusted (from 10 to 50 shares per preferred share). Analysts modeling fully diluted share counts or as-converted valuations using the S-1\'s post-split conversion terms must ensure their implied share prices are also on a post-split basis to correctly calculate conversion premiums, ownership percentages, and implied enterprise values.\n\n### 5. Historical Trend Analysis\nBecause the S-1 retroactively adjusts all periods (2023, 2024, 2025, Q1 2025, Q1 2026), any time-series analysis of per-share metrics (e.g., EPS growth trends, book value per share trajectory) is internally consistent on a post-split basis. Introducing unadjusted pre-split market prices into such an analysis would create a structural discontinuity that invalidates trend-based conclusions.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** The split-adjusted equivalent of Forge Global\'s ~$634 pre-split peak is **$126.80 per share**. Every per-share metric in the SpaceX S-1 — EPS, weighted average shares, pro forma EPS, net tangible book value per share, conversion ratios, and outstanding share counts — is presented on a post-split basis. Failure to adjust pre-split secondary market prices by dividing by 5 before comparing them to any S-1 per-share figure will produce a 5× systematic error in all derived valuation multiples.\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026)"\n    },\n    {\n      "url": "https://forgeglobal.com/spacex_stock",\n      "name": "Forge Global - SpaceX Stock Page"\n    }\n  ]\n}'})
